The paper deals with multi-agent transport task problems, which involve coordination and planning among multiple agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a Task Conflict-Based Search (TCBS) Algorithm to solve the problem optimally, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The problem also involves path planning, which suggests that it may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses experimental results and compares its solver with different sub-optimal ones, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and decision-making, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
